# User Story: CALJACK-001

**Status**: IMPLEMENTED

---

## User Story

**Title**: Main Menu and Game Window Foundation

**As a**: Player

**I want**: To launch the California Jack game and see a main menu with options

**So that**: I can start a new game or access help before playing

---

## Out of Scope

- Actual gameplay (see CALJACK-002)
- Help screen content (see CALJACK-006)
- Scoring display (see CALJACK-004)

---

## Assumptions

- **Assumption (explicit)**: Game runs on Windows desktop (primary target)
- **Assumption (explicit)**: Pygame is the GUI framework
- **Assumption (explicit)**: Fixed window size of 1024x768

---

## Acceptance Criteria (bulleted, testable)

- [x] Game launches a pygame window (1024x768)
- [x] Main menu displays "New Game" button
- [x] Main menu displays "Help" button
- [x] Clicking "New Game" transitions to game screen (placeholder for CALJACK-002)
- [x] Clicking "Help" transitions to help screen (placeholder for CALJACK-006)

---

## Non-functional Requirements

- Window responds to close button ✅
- Menu buttons respond within 100ms ✅

---

## Telemetry / Metrics Expected

- None

---

## Rollout / Rollback Notes

- Initial release; creates foundation for subsequent stories
- Ensure pygame in requirements.txt
